01/10/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The government decided on Thursday (September 30th) to end mandatory military service, effective January 1st 2011.
As of then, military service will be only for those who volunteer to join the army, pending parliamentary approval of the government's decision.
Authorities have repeatedly said they plan to professionalise the armed forces, to bring them in line with international standards.
(Tanjug, Politika, RTS, Beta - 30/09/10)
